paresse.xml

This package provides a means of typing "easily" greek letters
with the least possible effort ;) It takes care only of the
letters which have a macro name as \alpha or \Omega.

If you're running a *nix, you can use the provided Makefile.
For help type 'make help'.

You can obtain the doc 
(complete with commented code if \OnlyDescription is commented out) 
with english-paresse.dtx. 

Just latex (or pdflatex) it once then
  makeindex -s gind english-paresse
  makeindex -s gglo -o english-paresse.gls english-paresse.glo
then latex (or pdflatex) it once again.

Or use the provided Makefile and type 'make englishdoc'.

Happy TeXing and all that. 

